[1]
Date: Sat, 11 May 2002 16:07:09 +0200
From: "Steve Toovey" <toovey@travelclinic.co.za>
Source: Natal Mercury, 9 May 2002

Vibrio vulnificus kills wader in Durban
-----------------------------------------------------
A 55 year old South African died from V vulnificus infection after collecting
sand prawns, wading in shallow water in Durban harbour. The victim, "became
ill within a few days of wading in the harbour". A spokesman for McCord
Hospital and a Durban microbiologist "both confirmed that V vulnifiucs
infections were rarely reported" in South Africa. Further details such as
presenting symptoms, method of diagnosis, presence or absence of complicating
factors, treatment and clinical course are unknown.
--
